alendar, access the patient's health record during the call, take notes, and create consultation documents, prescriptions, or lab orders afterward.\"},{\"question\":\"Do patients and providers receive reminders about video consultations?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Automated reminders are sent for scheduled telemedicine appointments, payments, and follow-ups. Notifications can be delivered by email, SMS, or push to reduce no-shows and keep everyone prepared.\"},{\"question\":\"Do patients need special apps for telemedicine visits?\",\"answer\":\"No. Patients simply log in through your branded patient portal or mobile app. Telehealth video consultations run directly inside the Virtual Practice—no third-party downloads required.\"},{\"question\":\"Can I bill for telehealth visits the same way as in-person consultations?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Telemedicine appointments are defined like in-person services. You can set duration, service charges, and taxes; patients pay online; and billing records are generated automatically.\"},{\"question\":\"What happens to notes from a video consultation?\",\"answer\":\"Notes taken during the video consultation are stored in the encounter log. Providers can use them to generate consultation documents, prescriptions, or lab orders. If AI Scribe is used, these notes are included as context for creating clinical documentation.\"},{\"question\":\"Can more than one person join a telemedicine call?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Providers can invite caregivers, translators, or additional participants for instant video calls. An assisted video mode also lets nurses or staff help patients in remote areas connect to their provider.\"},{\"question\":\"Are telehealth video consultations secure and compliant?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. All telemedicine visits are encrypted and compliant with HIPAA, GDPR, and other healthcare regulations. White-labelling is optional—you may keep the standard look or customize the portal and apps to reflect your brand.\"},{\"question\":\"What 